Document: CanvasItemMaterial
Path: godot/classes/class_canvasitemmaterial.rst
Summary: Describes CanvasItemMaterial's purpose in modifying textures for CanvasItems, focusing on blend and lighting behaviors.

CanvasItemMaterials provide a means of modifying the textures associated with a CanvasItem. They specialize in describing blend and lighting behaviors for textures. Use a ShaderMaterial to more fully customize a material's interactions with a CanvasItem.
---CHUNK---
Document: CanvasItemMaterial
Path: godot/classes/class_canvasitemmaterial.rst
Summary: This section details the properties available for the CanvasItemMaterial class in Godot Engine.

Properties:
* BlendMode blend_mode (int): Controls the transparency and blending behavior of the material. Default: 0.
* LightMode light_mode (int): Determines how light interacts with the material. Default: 0.
* particles_anim_h_frames (int): The number of horizontal frames in a particle animation texture.
* particles_anim_loop (bool): If true, the particle animation will loop.
* particles_anim_v_frames (int): The number of vertical frames in a particle animation texture.
* particles_animation (bool): If true, enables particle animation. Default: false.
---CHUNK---
Document: CanvasItemMaterial
Path: godot/classes/class_canvasitemmaterial.rst
Summary: Defines the blend and light modes for CanvasItem materials.

Enumerations:
BlendMode:
  BLEND_MODE_MIX (0): Mix blending mode. Colors are assumed to be independent of the alpha (opacity) value.
  BLEND_MODE_ADD (1): Additive blending mode.
  BLEND_MODE_SUB (2): Subtractive blending mode.
  BLEND_MODE_MUL (3): Multiplicative blending mode.
  BLEND_MODE_PREMULT_ALPHA (4): Mix blending mode. Colors are assumed to be premultiplied by the alpha (opacity) value.

LightMode:
  LIGHT_MODE_NORMAL (0): Render the material using both light and non-light sensitive material properties.
  LIGHT_MODE_UNSHADED (1): Render the material as if there were no light.
  LIGHT_MODE_LIGHT_ONLY (2): Render the material as if there were only light.
---CHUNK---
Document: CanvasItemMaterial
Path: godot/classes/class_canvasitemmaterial.rst
Summary: Describes the properties of the CanvasItemMaterial class, including blend mode, light mode, and particle animation settings.

Property: blend_mode
Type: BlendMode
Description: The manner in which a material's rendering is applied to underlying textures.
Setters: set_blend_mode(value: BlendMode)
Getters: get_blend_mode() -> BlendMode

Property: light_mode
Type: LightMode
Description: The manner in which material reacts to lighting.
Setters: set_light_mode(value: LightMode)
Getters: get_light_mode() -> LightMode

Property: particles_anim_h_frames
Type: int
Description: The number of columns in the spritesheet assigned as Texture2D for a GPUParticles2D or CPUParticles2D.
Note: This property is only used and visible in the editor if particles_animation is true.
Setters: set_particles_anim_h_frames(value: int)
Getters: get_particles_anim_h_frames() -> int

Property: particles_anim_loop
Type: bool
Description: If true, the particles animation will loop.
Note: This property is only used and visible in the editor if particles_animation is true.
Setters: set_particles_anim_loop(value: bool)
Getters: get_particles_anim_loop() -> bool

Property: particles_anim_v_frames
Type: int
Description: The number of rows in the spritesheet assigned as Texture2D for a GPUParticles2D or CPUParticles2D.
Note: This property is only used and visible in the editor if particles_animation is true.
Setters: set_particles_anim_v_frames(value: int)
Getters: get_particles_anim_v_frames() -> int

Property: particles_animation
Type: bool
Default: false
Description: If true, enable spritesheet-based animation features when assigned to GPUParticles2D and CPUParticles2D nodes. The ParticleProcessMaterial.anim_speed_max or CPUParticles2D.anim_speed_max should also be set to a positive value for the animation to play. This property (and other particles_anim_* properties that depend on it) has no effect on other types of nodes.
Setters: set_particles_animation(value: bool)
Getters: get_particles_animation() -> bool